				<div class="article-unit article-unit-img-wrapper group">
						<div class="article-unit-img">
<a href="http://financecareers.about.com/od/careerstrategiestactics/fl/Promotion-in-Place.htm" data-component="expertLandingPageRecentArticles" data-source="ArticleSite_Latest" data-type="article.image" data-ordinal="5"><img data-original="http://f.tqn.com/y/financecareers/1/V/o/0/-/-/493173915-crop.jpg" alt="Increased Pay and Prestige - Sorbetto/iStock Vectors/Getty Images" width="215" height="143" data-load="lazy" class="" >
</a>						</div>
					<div class="article-unit-desc">
						<h5 class="heading">
							<a href="http://financecareers.about.com/od/careerstrategiestactics/fl/Promotion-in-Place.htm" data-component="expertLandingPageRecentArticles" data-source="ArticleSite_Latest" data-type="article.heading" data-ordinal="5">What is a Promotion in Place?</a>
						</h5>
							<a href="http://financecareers.about.com/od/careerstrategiestactics/fl/Promotion-in-Place.htm" data-component="expertLandingPageRecentArticles" data-source="ArticleSite_Latest" data-type="article.blurb" data-ordinal="5" class="article-blurb">When you receive a better job title while retaining the same position, this represents a promotion in place. This is a common scenario in may firms.</a>
						<div><div class="share-options-container open-right with-msg">
<div class="share-btns share-options popout"
data-url="http://financecareers.about.com/od/careerstrategiestactics/fl/Promotion-in-Place.htm"
data-social-title="What is a Promotion in Place?"
data-description="When you receive a better job title while retaining the same position, this represents a promotion in place. This is a common scenario in may firms."
